Network Scanning

Network scanning is the process of discovering active hosts, open ports, and services running on a system. It helps security professionals understand a system before performing a security assessment.

Nmap

Nmap (Network Mapper) is an open-source tool used for network discovery and security auditing. It identifies live hosts, open ports, running services, and operating systems.

TCP

TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) provides reliable communication between devices by ensuring packets are delivered correctly.

UDP

UDP (User Datagram Protocol) is a connectionless protocol used for faster communication where reliability is less important.

Service Enumeration

Service enumeration identifies the applications and versions running on open ports. This helps determine potential vulnerabilities.

Operating System Detection

Nmap can identify the operating system by analyzing responses from the target host. This information assists penetration testers in selecting appropriate testing techniques.

Banner Grabbing

Banner grabbing retrieves information from network services to determine software names and versions.

Vulnerability Assessment

A vulnerability assessment identifies security weaknesses in systems before attackers can exploit them.